<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Globus_Cassus&amp;action=edit&amp;section=11" title="Edit section: Literature">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Literature</span></h2>
<div class="thumb tright">
<div class="thumbinner" style="width:130px;"><a href="/wiki/File:Globus_Cassus_2004_book_cover.jpg" class="image" title="Book cover"><img alt="" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/f/f0/Globus_Cassus_2004_book_cover.jpg" width="128" height="175" border="0" class="thumbimage" /></a>
<div class="thumbcaption">
<div class="magnify"><a href="/wiki/File:Globus_Cassus_2004_book_cover.jpg" class="internal" title="Enlarge"><img src="/skins-1.5/common/images/magnify-clip.png" width="15" height="11" alt="" /></a></div>
Book cover</div>
</div>
</div>
<p><i>Globus Cassus</i>, Lars Müller Publishers, with contributions by <a href="/wiki/Boris_Groys" title="Boris Groys">Boris Groys</a>, <a href="/w/index.php?title=Claude_Lichtenstein&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Claude Lichtenstein (page does not exist)">Claude Lichtenstein</a>, <a href="/w/index.php?title=Michael_Stauffer&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Michael Stauffer (page does not exist)">Michael Stauffer</a> and Christian Waldvogel. Awarded the Gold Medal in international competition "Best designed books from all over the World 2004", (<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/3037780452" class="internal">ISBN 3-03778-045-2</a>)</p>
